text: even when I chose to be a software
engineer my focus was to create software
or help create software that would
impact people's lives in a good way I
didn't start coding until like three or
four years ago and I wish I'd started
earlier I used my first ec2 instance as
a virtual machine in one of my computer
information systems classes at the local
community college it was very easy to
set up and I was amazed at how quickly I
got used to it I some going into the IT
field like that is amazing to have
because usually you're responsible for
installing the software and then you're
responsible for the troubleshooting so
the easy setup is what got me into cloud
computing eventually took a cloud
computing essentials class and that
wasn't enough for me so I learned a lot
about DevOps and my software development
engineer pathway which was something
that I haven't quite touched on in any
of the programs that I've been in so far
definitely helped inform me that there's
more to software development I just
landed my first software engineering job
about two weeks ago
and during the whole interviewing
process with this company and other
companies I was asked if I had prior
experience with AWS and I was
confidently able to say yes because I
did X Y & Z in these pathways with AWS
educate so I think it definitely helped
me in securing my job now
